using words like "overreact,"

01:55.430 --> 01:56.760
We should really
be looking at --

01:56.770 --> 01:58.170
I think the word "over-react" came up

01:58.180 --> 02:00.610
Because the doctor always
said he had an alibi,

02:00.620 --> 02:02.640
That he'd been on a
boat trip with a friend

02:02.650 --> 02:03.710
During the time of the murder.

02:03.720 --> 02:06.110
And today,that friend showed up.

02:06.120 --> 02:08.960
Well,then we'll hear what the guy has t

02:08.970 --> 02:11.039
But if the police have evidence

02:11.050 --> 02:14.160
Connecting a specific
individual to murder,

02:14.170 --> 02:16.420
Do you want them to
keep it to themselves,

02:16.430 --> 02:19.580
Or do you want to present
that evidence in court

02:19.590 --> 02:21.410
And let the justice system decide?

02:21.420 --> 02:22.660
Let me add something,

02:22.670 --> 02:24.910
That even though deputy chief johnson

02:24.920 --> 02:28.670
Did not get a confession
this time in this case,

02:28.680 --> 02:31.990
I have every confidence that
she made the right arrest

02:32.000 --> 02:34.290
And that she will ultimately prevail.

02:34.300 --> 02:36.080
Could you turn that off,please?

02:37.440 --> 02:39.880
Taylor's throwing you to the wolves.

02:39.890 --> 02:42.660
Or maybe just giving
them a map to your body.

02:43.540 --> 02:46.750
So,tough time in court
this afternoon,huh?

02:50.670 --> 02:53.610
Hey,are you mad at me about something?

02:53.620 --> 02:55.550
I just had a bad day is all.

02:55.560 --> 02:58.400
